{
  "stem": "6052.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And surely not after Hitler, but even could not practice his profession as-- as trader.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was very, very difficult because, at that time already, 'Don't buy from Jews' and 'Boycott the Jews.' And all this was a slogan over Germany.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was an enormous, enormous hardship on all of us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And now, coming back to the point where I was sent by the Leipzig-- the Israelitische Religionsgemeinde, to Steckelsdorf, near Berlin, which is a Hachshara camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "At-- at that time, I did not know all the possible ramifications, and I did not know what further developed in Leipzig, where my brother remained and my sisters remained at that time, and my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And everybody were-- was still alive, which was in the year 1939-- something like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was again a matter of luck-- luck.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were two-- two people from our city, Oskar Deutsche and I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were the only ones who were sent from the Israelitische Religionsgemeinde zu Leipzig.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Apparently, from each city they got a number of spaces to-- or a number of people they could send there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Over there, I believe we were over 100 children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I don't know how I was chosen, but I was lucky, and I am forever grateful to the Israelitische Religionsgemeinde, whom I still correspond with.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every New Year's, I send them a-- a Happy New Year.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's the Religion-- this was the congregation of the-- of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was established, if my memory does not mislead me, by Carlebach, or in the time of Carlebach, who was a great teacher and rabbi over there-- a great man.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he died before the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I believe it was the year 1936, 1937.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
